LabelEncoder для категориальных признаков¶

LabelEncoder.

In [7]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

def number_encode_features(df):
    result = df.copy() 
    encoders = {}
    for column in result.columns:
        if result.dtypes[column] == 'object':
            encoders[column] = LabelEncoder() 
            result[column] = encoders[column].fit_transform(result[column])
    return result, encoders

In [15]:
#    supervised 
def plot_supervised_metrics(completeness_scores, homogeneity_scores, v_measure_scores, adjusted_rand_scores):
    plt.figure(figsize=(25,12))

    ax1 = plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
    ax1.set_title('Completeness_score per n_clusters')
    sns.lineplot(x = list(completeness_scores.keys()), y = list(completeness_scores.values()), marker = 'o', ax = ax1)
    ax1.set_xlabel('n_clusters')
    ax1.set_ylabel('completeness_score')

    ax2 = plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
    ax2.set_title('Homogeneity_score per n_clusters')
    sns.lineplot(x = list(homogeneity_scores.keys()), y = list(homogeneity_scores.values()), marker = 'o', ax = ax2)
    ax2.set_xlabel('n_clusters')
    ax2.set_ylabel('homogeneity_score')

    ax3 = plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
    ax3.set_title('V_measure_score per n_clusters')
    sns.lineplot(x = list(v_measure_scores.keys()), y = list(v_measure_scores.values()), marker = 'o', ax = ax3)
    ax3.set_xlabel('n_clusters')
    ax3.set_ylabel('v_measure_score')

    ax4 = plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
    ax4.set_title('Adjusted_rand_score per n_clusters')
    sns.lineplot(x = list(adjusted_rand_scores.keys()), y = list(adjusted_rand_scores.values()), marker = 'o', ax = ax4)
    ax4.set_xlabel('n_clusters')
    ax4.set_ylabel('adjusted_rand_score')

    plt.show()

Kmeans Clustering¶

In [16]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.metrics import completeness_score, homogeneity_score, v_measure_score, adjusted_rand_score
from tqdm import tqdm
In [17]:
completeness_scores = {}
homogeneity_scores = {} 
v_measure_scores = {} 
adjusted_rand_scores = {}

n_clusters_grid = np.arange(2, 11)

for n_clusters in tqdm(n_clusters_grid):
    model = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters, init='k-means++', random_state=42)
    labels = model.fit_predict(X)
    
    completeness_scores[n_clusters] = completeness_score(y, labels)
    homogeneity_scores[n_clusters] = homogeneity_score(y, labels)
    v_measure_scores[n_clusters] = v_measure_score(y, labels)
    adjusted_rand_scores[n_clusters] = adjusted_rand_score(y, labels)
